{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7cb69065-f1de-4b5e-87d3-d32da589f550","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types from files listed *above* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Mvk71r6KPgmn7uk2F4nQMg","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Fixing F# file order"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Ha7hYCJGo5K9zD1bmuHh2J","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-c9e00af6e0ae41f1858080483f69c0d3/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-c9e00af6e0ae41f1858080483f69c0d3/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"09da7ccd-0932-48f1-8008-8ffffd48eec7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear *before* them in the project file. \n\nIn the `.fsproj`, `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`). The fix is to reorder the `<Compile>` items so `Domain.fs` comes first, then `Services.fs`, then `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":397,"requestId":"4412:252559:17ACD4D:1ABD140:69FE8502"},"id":"f4aedd54-8082-4319-85ee-92c1321ae6c6","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:51:21.825Z","parentId":"48f4a5ff-b7f3-47f8-9713-70ea179a7e5e"}
